(thirdQuint)FUSION Regimen: Combined Pro re Nata and Fixed Regimen Ranibizumab in Exudative Age-related Macular Degeneration.

 This is a prospective, open-label, consecutive interventional case series in treatment-naive patients with exudative AMD.

 A loading phase of 2-3 injections is followed by a fixed-interval regimen of injections combined with a pro re nata regimen for 12 months.

 Endpoints include VA, presence of fluid at spectral domain optical coherent tomography (SD-OCT), adverse events and number of injections administered.

