The purpose of this study is to investigate the safety and efficacy of a combined fixed-interval and a pro re nata (PRN) regimens of ranibizumab (FUSION regimen) for the treatment of exudative age-related macular degeneration (AMD) in patients with good visual acuity (VA) at baseline.

 To establish whether similar efficacy to monthly regimens can be achieved with fewer injections, even in patients with good VA.

